{
  "stem": "11723.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And also after a few days of being there, I started getting lice.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And a few days later, they put me in a barber's chair and they shaved my head completely.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And I remember looking in the mirror.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I didn't recognize myself.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And I was crying.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "They shaved my sister, too.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And we looked like two little idiots, two little melons.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And then we both got sick.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I had everything from ringworm to TB-- mild case of TB.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And Susan got real sick.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Now, I always felt responsible for her because I was the big sister, and also, she was my only family.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "I mean, I had a reunion with my mother-- a short one, overnight.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "But who-- I didn't know whether I was going to see her again.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "So my sister was my only family.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And they took her to an infirmary because she had fever, and I was so scared that I'm not going to see her again either.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And then I'm all alone in the world.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And I-- I remember I used to sneak into the room where they took her just to see if she was still there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And I was also sick, but I was in better condition than she was because I was older.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And liberation came to us in April in that place because-- although by that time, most everything was liberated.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "My parents couldn't come for us because there were no bridges still.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "So the day that they opened the first temporary bridge, my mother and uncle Regeur came to get us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "They went to the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And again, they were told they don't know where we are.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
